</dt>
</center></div>
<dd>The <a href="http://nesea.nrel.gov/">American Tour de Sol</a> is an eight day electric and solar vehicle road rally event from Connecticut to Maine 
started in 1989 by the Northeast Sustainable Energy Association of Greenfield, MA . The event has grown to a rally of 
international significance, showcasing 50 vehicles from North America and abroad. <br>
</dd>
